  <title>Introduction</title>

  <para>This owner's manual describes the Dutch-built Luxe-motor live-aboard
  barge <emphasis>Beatrice</emphasis> (registered in the UK as
  <emphasis>Beatrice of Hull</emphasis>).</para>

  <para><emphasis>Beatrice</emphasis> was commissioned in 2015 by Paul and
  Diane Reeve <email>paulanddiane@pdjr.eu</email> from the builder
  Scheepsreparatie Friesland (SRF) based in Harlingen, NL. The ship was
  launched in Harlingen on 6 August 2017 with hand-over in August 2018.</para>

  <para>This manual describes the ship and its installed equipment together
  with explanations of its systems and guidance on their operation: it is not
  a comprehensive or definitive text and documentation supplied by the
  manufacturers of all installed equipment is considered an essential and
  authoritative adjunct.</para>

  <para>This manual and manufacturer's manuals are intended to be useful
  orientation and maintenance guides, but in case of difficulty you should
  refer to the boat builder or the manufacturer of the installation in
  question. </para>

  <para>Always use trained and competent people for maintenance, repairs and
  modifications: in particular, modifications that may affect the safety
  characteristics of the craft must be assessed, executed and documented by
  competent people and the boat builder cannot be held responsible for
  modifications which they have not approved.</para>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">PLEASE KEEP THIS MANUAL IN A SECURE PLACE, AND
  HAND IT OVER TO THE NEW OWNER WHEN YOU SELL THE CRAFT</emphasis></para>

  <section>
    <title>Conventions used in the text</title>

    <section>
      <title>Warnings of hazard</title>

      <para>A range of warning symbols derived from a yellow triangle with a
      black border (see following section) are used to indicate hazards or
      unsafe practices which will could result in damage to the vessel or the
      injury or death of its operators.</para>
    </section>

